definition: Austria/Austrian/abbr. for 奧地利|奥地利[Ao4 di4 li4]/Olympic/Olympics/abbr. for 奧林匹克|奥林匹克[Ao4 lin2 pi3 ke4]
fourth of the ten Heavenly Stems 十天干[shi2 tian1 gan1]/fourth in order/letter "D" or Roman "IV" in list "A, B, C", or "I, II, III" etc/ancient Chinese compass point: 195°/butyl/cubes (of food)

sentences.english: It is said Odin sacrifice one of his eye to gain the water of the wisdom under the World Tree.
sentences.chinese: 据说他的眼睛奥丁牺牲下获得世界之树的智慧水面。

sentences.english: Odin hopes his son will learn humility among the earthlings.
sentences.chinese: 奥丁希望他的儿子在地球的生灵中学会谦卑。

sentences.english: Odin can help you here as well.
sentences.chinese: 奥丁可以帮你在这里一样。

sentences.english: Rajesh: By Odin's beard, this is good Chex Mix.
sentences.chinese: 奥丁的胡子，这是不错的早餐混合物。

sentences.english: He swore to defeat Odin's plan.
sentences.chinese: 他发誓一定要挫败奥丁的计划。

sentences.english: What Odin whispered In Baldr's ear.
sentences.chinese: 奥丁在儿子耳边的话语。

sentences.english: The Champion represents Odin's divine force of retribution.
sentences.chinese: 魔战士代表着奥丁神的审判之力。

sentences.english: And he killed Odin who is the top of Gods in "Ragnarok".
sentences.chinese: 他杀死奥丁是谁在“仙境传说”神的顶部。

sentences.english: He is a son of Odin and Jord, and one of the most powerful gods.
sentences.chinese: 他是奥丁跟乔德之子，也是其中一位最强大的神。

sentences.english: The gods were Odin, Thor and Freya.
sentences.chinese: 神人奥丁，索尔和芙蕾雅。

sentences.english: Odin also knew that who will die and alive in the end.
sentences.chinese: 奥丁也知道，谁就会死去，最后还活着。

sentences.english: Odin, who is the wisdom of Gods, and also the head of all Gods in Norse.
sentences.chinese: 奥丁，谁是神的智慧，也是在北欧诸神头。

sentences.english: He's a lecherous old god by the name of Odin .
sentences.chinese: 他是一个名为奥丁的好色古神。

definition: Lucifer (Satan's name before his fall in Jewish and Christian mythology)
Poseidon, God of the sea in Greek mythology
Loki, god of fire and mischievous destroyer in Norse mythology
Titan (race of deities in Greek mythology, moon of Saturn etc)
